            <h3 style="color:#000;">Risk Improvement Chart</h3>
            <p class="contentP">
                As shown below, we have completed an enhancement to the current <strong>Risk Improvement Chart</strong>, which depicts the risk improvement over the life of the program, by adding an 
                additional column to the <strong>Improved</strong> risk.
            </p>
            <p class="contentP">
                This is now a two-page report with the second page providing a rolling five-year analysis of their risk improvements.  The chart on the left side identifies the number of new recommendations 
                for that calendar year (blue bar) along with the number of recommendation closed for that calendar year (green bar).  The chart on the right contains the <strong>Identified</strong> and <strong>Improved</strong> risks in 
                association with the recommendation counts by year.
            </p>
            <p class="contentP">
                <strong>Note:</strong>  This is not an interactive tool due to the complexity of the various statistical breakdowns.  
            </p>
            <p class="contentP">
                This enhanced chart is now available in TUV SUD GRC Connect, which can be accessed under the <strong>Site Map > Output Reports > All Recommendations > Risk Improvement Chart.</strong>
                This is available for both Fire and Boiler & Machinery.
            </p>
